The Enterprise Intelligence Solution Architect is responsible for providing
expertise and thought leadership for planning, management, formulation and
development of Solution Architectures in the specialised areas of data and
intelligence.

The role is business outcome focussed and drives innovation and agility
through solutions that will deliver business and technology change/s in
support of core organisational functions, business strategies, Digital
strategies and operational Enterprise Architecture plans.

** The Solution Architect Key Accountabilities include: **

  * Identify, resolve and manage architecture challenges throughout the provisioning of technical solutions across the organisation; 
  * Provide expert advice in Solution Architecture and Design/s for the organisation whilst maintaining a focus on business objectives; 
  * Development and management of relationships with key clients to support the identification, coordination and planning of services; 
  * Ensuring that new initiatives and projects are identified, defined and aligned with business plans; 
  * Identification, resolution and management of strategy and architecture issues / exemptions are identified, resolved and managed; 
  * Provision of appropriate advice regarding architecture options / solutions to other projects and initiatives; and 
  * Production of architecture design artefacts. 

** Technical Requirements include: **

  * Strong experience in delivering large scale data and intelligence solutions that are customer focused, easy to consume and create business impact in hybrid environments (on-premise and multi-cloud); 
  * Strong experience in designing and implementing large scale cloud data ecosystems that comply with cyber and information security requirements; 
  * Designing end-to-end cloud-based solutions that are highly available, scalable, stable, secure and cost-effective; 
  * Experience in designing and implementing cloud migration strategies for on premise data warehousing and analytical solutions; 
  * Experience in commercial documentation and negotiations related to product or application assessment, tenders and commercial agreements; and 
  * Highly skilled in communicating across different levels within the organisation, able to explain technical issues and IT solution strategies to stakeholders. 

** Selection Criteria **

Selection of the successful bid will be based on the following criteria:

** Essential Criteria: **

  * Significant solution delivery experience in large scale data systems across both on premise and cloud environments; 
  * Significant experience in architecture, design and building of enterprise level data models, data pipelines, data migrations and data quality management; 
  * Demonstrated understanding of data management tools including: 
    * On prem - SAP Data Services, SAP BusinessObjects, IBM Data Stage, SAP Hana, Oracle Exadata, SharePlex; 
    * Cloud - SAP Data Services, SAP BusinessObjects, SAP Hana, S3, DMS, DataBricks, Tableau, Power BI, AWS S3; 
  * Demonstrated experience working with data governance functions and teams; 
  * Ability to elicit business and architectural information from others and document it as part of solution designs, including demonstration of how solutions meet frameworks and standards; 
  * Demonstrated ability to communicate effectively with business and technical stakeholders, senior management and project team members, including running workshops and producing artefacts from these engagements; and 
  * Demonstrated track record of meeting deadlines in a high pressure, fast paced environment while managing multiple projects or work packages. 

** Desirable Criteria: **

  * Hands on experience in implementing data ingestion routines both real time and batch using best practices in data modelling, ETL / ELT processes by leveraging AWS technologies and big data tools; 
  * Experience in both modernising data platforms with cloud solutions and optimising environments with data already on a cloud platform; 
  * Software engineering background with coding ability in languages like Python / Scala; and 
  * AWS cloud certification (preferred). 

** Duration **

12-month contract.

** Reporting Structure **

The role will report to the Business Analysis & Initiation Lead.

